    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_dæræn" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>dæræn</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>разбросанное, неубранное сено</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>scattered, not gathered hay</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>раскиданные, несвязанные снопы</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>scattered, unbound sheaves</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>разгром</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>defeat</q>
                    </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">новейшем употреблении
                        вообще</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in modern language in
                        general</note></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>dæræn kænyn</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>разбрасывать</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>scatter</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>раскидать</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>throw out</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>громить (например, врага)</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>smash (for example, enemy)</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>xwasʒaw dæx cid dæræni fælmænæj æxecæn paraxat listæn
                            ærkænidæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>косарь из мягкой кучи травы делал себе пышную постель</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the mower made himself a puffy bed of a soft pile of grass</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"
                            /><biblScope>6</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Ʒаххо æma Marta sæ dæræni særǧi ragi ærlæwdtæncæ, sæ kustbæl
                            oduncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Дзаххо и Марта давно стали у своей (подлежащей уборке) кучи сена,
                                ревностно работают</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Dzakhho and Marta have been at their heaps of hay (to be harvested)
                                long time ago, they are working zealously</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"
                            /><biblScope>31</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Точно соответствует <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>daraṇa-</w>
                        <gloss><q>взрывание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>лопание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ломание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>разгром</q></gloss></mentioned>. Заключает глагольную основу
                    %idar%i- (<mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
                        <w>*der-</w></mentioned>) ‘разрывать’, ‘разбрасывать’, ‘рассеивать’ и т. п.
                    Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>darrīdan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                        ><w>darīdan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>darītan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>dariyān</w></mentioned>,<note type="footnote" n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note>
                    <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>dirag</w>
                        <gloss><q>рвать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>раздирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>darra</w>
                        <gloss><q>отломанный кусок</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>щепка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>darānā</w>
                        <gloss><q>быть соскобленным</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>dar-</w>
                        <gloss><q>отдирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>разрывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>dar- (dṛṇāti)</w>
                        <gloss><q>разрываться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>рассеиваться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>dārayati</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"
                            >каузативно</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">causative</note>
                        <gloss><q>разбивать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>рассеивать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>разгромить (врага)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>tʼerem</w>
                        <gloss><q>я сдираю</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>дьрати</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>драть</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>деру</w></mentioned>,
                    а также <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>у-дар-ять</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                        ><w>дрань</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                    ><w>драка</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>derù</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><w>dirti</w>
                        <gloss><q>сдирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>teran</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/>
                        <w>ga-taíran</w>
                        <gloss><q>разрывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>разрушать</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">
                                (<mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                                <w>zehren</w></mentioned>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                (<mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                                <w>zehren</w></mentioned>)</note></mentioned>,<mentioned
                        xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>torn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>zorn</w>
                        <gloss><q>гнев</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>δέρω</w>
                        <gloss><q>сдираю (шкуру, кору и т. п.)</q></gloss></mentioned>. Из
                    осетинского идет <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>dərən</w>
                        <gloss><q>разбросанное сено</q></gloss></mentioned>. С удлинением %iz%i
                    основа %idar%i- налична в ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dærzæg"/> ‘шершавый’
                    и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævdærzyn"/> ‘натирать кожу’; см. эти
                            слова.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>163</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">This words exactly corresponds to <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>daraṇa-</w>
                        <gloss><q>explosing</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>bursting</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>breaking</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>crushing</q></gloss></mentioned>. There is a verbal stem %idar%i-
                        (<mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
                        <w>*der-</w></mentioned>) ‘tear’, ‘scatter’, ‘disperse’ etc. Cf. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>darrīdan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                        ><w>darīdan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>darītan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>dariyān</w></mentioned>,%l1%l<note type="footnote" n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note>
                    <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>dirag</w>
                        <gloss><q>rip</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>tear to pieces</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>darra</w>
                        <gloss><q>broken piece</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>chip</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>darānā</w>
                        <gloss><q>be erased</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>dar-</w>
                        <gloss><q>tear off</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>tear to pieces</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>dar- (dṛṇāti)</w>
                        <gloss><q>be torn</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>scatter</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>dārayati</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"
                            >каузативно</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">causative</note>
                        <gloss><q>break</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>scatter</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>defeat (enemy)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>tʼerem</w>
                        <gloss><q>I tear off</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>dьrati</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>drat'</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>deru</w></mentioned>,
                    and also <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>u-dar-yat'</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                        ><w>dran'</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                    ><w>draka</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>derù</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><w>dirti</w>
                        <gloss><q>tear off</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>teran</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/>
                        <w>ga-taíran</w>
                        <gloss><q>tear to pieces</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>break</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<mentioned
                                xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                                <w>zehren</w></mentioned>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                (<mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                                <w>zehren</w></mentioned>)</note></mentioned>,<mentioned
                        xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>torn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>zorn</w>
                        <gloss><q>anger</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>δέρω</w>
                        <gloss><q>I skin (an animal)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>I bark (a tree)</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>dərən</w>
                        <gloss><q>scattered hay</q></gloss></mentioned> comes from Ossetic. The stem
                    %idar%i- with a lengthened %iz%i <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dærzæg"/> ‘rough’
                    and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævdærzyn"/> ‘rub skin’; see this
                            words.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>163</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="ru" n="1">Существует и <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><w>dirandin</w>
                        <gloss><q>déchirer</q></gloss></mentioned>?</note>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="en" n="1">Does <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><w>dirandin</w>
                        <gloss><q>déchirer</q></gloss></mentioned> exist too?</note>
            </entry>
        </body>
